=== Approach ===

10k queries to be studied and perhaps modified.

Data Definition Language (DDL) will require separate versions for Oracle and Postgres, e.g.
CREATE TABLE, CREATE FUNCTION, CREATE INDEX.  These statements are centralized and change rarely so it is easy to maintain two versions.

Non-DDL queries will fall into four categories:
        o  works unchanged
        o  can be rewritten to work on both, e.g. ANSI joins, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
        o  (same) but requires db changes, e.g. add compatibility functions like decode()
        o  need to add Postgres-specific version the query


Mark queries via comments?  '-- PGPORT'



